@startuml VPtr_Multiple_Inheritance
!theme plain

title vptr in Multiple Inheritance - Multiple vptrs

class Base1 {
  + virtual void f()
  - int a
}

class Base2 {
  + virtual void g()
  - int b
}

class Derived {
  + void f() override
  + void g() override
  - int c
}

Base1 <|-- Derived
Base2 <|-- Derived

note right of Derived
  **Memory Layout:**
  [vptr1][a]    ← Base1 subobject
  [vptr2][b]    ← Base2 subobject
  [c]           ← Derived data
  
  **TWO vptrs!**
  One for each base class
  
  vptr1 → Derived vtable for Base1
  vptr2 → Derived vtable for Base2
  
  **Size:** 8 + 4 + 8 + 4 + 4 = 28 bytes
end note

@enduml